        "title": "reGATE connection",
        "description": "Enter the MQTT host (IP) and port of the reGATE.\n\nHow to find the IP address:\n\n• From a terminal on your local network:\n  `arp -a` then look for a host containing \"gatexway\".\n\n• From the reGATE app:\n  Settings → reGATE information → find the host/IP.\n\n• You can also identify the device by its MAC address in your router/DHCP list.",
        "data": {
          "host": "Host / IP",
          "port": "Port",
          "prefix": "MQTT prefix"
        }
      },
      "telemetry": {
        "title": "Help extend reGATE support",
        "description": "Optional opt-in: when a new or unsupported MQTT profile is detected on your installation, Home Assistant can notify you with a **pre-filled GitHub link** (anonymized roles and MQTT key names).\n\nNothing is sent automatically — you decide whether to open the link. This helps prioritize actuators, schedulers, and new MQTT keys.\n\nYou can change this anytime under **reGATE → Configure**.",
        "data": {
          "telemetry": "Notify me about new or unsupported devices (recommended)"
        }
      }
    },
